		"body": "Fixes #14361\r\n\r\n### Summary\r\n`yarn install` fails in clean Linux build environments where `rsync` is not installed.  \r\nThis PR ensures the build process no longer fails when `rsync` is unavailable.\r\n\r\n### Changes\r\n- Handle missing `rsync` gracefully during build\r\n- Prevent yarn install from exiting with code 1\r\n- Improve compatibility with minimal Debian/Linux setups\r\n\r\n### Testing\r\n- Tested on clean Debian environment\r\n- Verified `yarn install` completes successfully without `rsync` preinstalled\r\n\r\nThis improves the developer experience when setting up the build environment from scratch.",
